{
  "type": "Collection",
  "id": "arceme-datacubes-global",
  "stac_version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Multi-sensor Earth observation data cubes for the compared global analysis of single versus multi-hazard extreme weather events from the ARCEME-DHP (Drought interrupted by Heavy Precipitation) database (see related resources), generated within the ARCEME project (Adaptation and Resilience to Climate Extremes and Multi-hazard Events). Each cube covers a 10 × 10 km area centred on the event's sampled location and integrates: Sentinel-2 L2A (13 bands + SCL, 10 m), Sentinel-1 RTC (VV + VH, 10 m), Copernicus DEM GLO-30 (10 m resampled), and ESA WorldCover 2020 (10 m). The temporal window spans ±12 months around the event date. Cloud masking is applied using SEnSeIv2/SegFormerB2. \nThe cubes are named \"DC__id_suffix__start__end.zarr\": the identifiers \"id\" refer to the DHP events labels in ARCEME-DHP. Two cube variants exist per event site — suffix \"_d\" (Drought-only) and \"_dhp\" (Drought interrupted by Heavy Precipitation). ",
